# English-Only Code

All **comments**, **variable names**, and **function names** in this repository must be written in **English**.

This applies to:
- XML documentation (`///`, `/** */`)
- Inline comments (`//`)
- Block comments (`/* */`)
- Variable names
- Function/method names

**Exceptions:**
- i18n translation files (e.g. `pl-PL/index.js`) contain user-facing strings in their target language – keep those as-is.
- **User-facing strings** – labels, messages, buttons and any text displayed to the user in the UI can be in Polish (or the app’s display language). E.g. `<span>Brak zdjęcia</span>`, `:label="'Wgraj zdjęcie'"`, `error.value = 'Nie udało się załadować zdjęcia.'` are fine in Polish.
- `ReportMenu.vue` – report content strings in `buildReportContent` stay in Polish (report content sent to backend).

```csharp
// ✅ GOOD
/// <summary>
/// Maps language variant to list of supported languages.
/// </summary>
const userName = "John";
function loadUserData() { }

// ❌ BAD
/// <summary>
/// Mapowanie wariantu językowego na listę obsługiwanych języków.
/// </summary>
const nazwaUzytkownika = "John";
function zaladujDaneUzytkownika() { }
```
